	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have been playing a cleric for some time now, and I love this class.  As far as weapons and armor goes the better stuff, just like in all other games, comes to you as you reach higher lvls.  But, and keep this in mind, unless you are soloing, at the higher levels you are almost ALWAYS going to be in a group.  There arent very many groups who like the cleric to get into melee, as they want us to be able to heal on the spot and not concentrate on anything else.  Ofcourse you can play your cleric however you like or choose, but just through experience, you will be medding and healing for the most part.  So, with all this said, in the beginning its whatever you like to weild, until you start grouping a lot, then its healing, healing, and more healing.  As you make friends in the game they will help you as far as letting you know what the best thing to  go for. (Or check the net)<br>Good luck with your cleric, and remember, we are in very high demand.  <br><br>Clayus<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
