<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96821347412491></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96821347412491><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=96821347412491>How to run away</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=607><span id=Sage>Gedran</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>97 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 6th 12:11 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A basic guide to running that can be used by all classes.<br>First off, if you don't know what vectoring is, or how to vector across a zone, read the posts that I think are now present on every page about vectoring.<br>Another method besides vectoring, is lagging the mob that is chasing you.  This is accomplished by using height difference barriers.  These include mostly walls that can be run over by the player, Exits to lakes and rivers, gating, Instant height increases (I.E. Lifts at Kelethin etc.) and large chasm'd cliffs.  While none of these barriers will completely drop a mob off of you, they may add enough lag distance between you and the mob for you to get away.  <br>Speaking for clerics, this class has a number of useful spells to help escape pursuing mobs.  These include, Divine aura (line), root, stun (line), and fear (line)<br><br>Divine Aura: This line of spells can be a life saver when your lvl 1 all the way to lvl 60.  It protects you no matter if you being hit by 2 damage blows or 200.  And it's so powerful, that Paladins don't even get it untill lvl 50.  Clerics get it at lvl 1.  With a one second cast time, and 18 seconds of invincibility, it is a spell that is not easily interuppted, and can easily save your life.<br>Root: A basic multi class spell that holds a mob in place.  Good for adding distance between you and it, while not letting it run wild.<br>Stun: While not lasting as long as most roots, stuns can interrupt casting, halt attacks, and at later lvl's do damage.  Mostly this is a battle spell, but it can be used to add a little distance between you (and your party) and the mob<br>Fear: A personal dislike of mine, yet it can be useful.  On top of getting the common spell fear, clerics also get fear undead which is limited to a few classes.  The good thing about fear, is that while your running one way, the mob is running the other, adding extra distance, however, along the way it's pulling things to aggro on you, and it never seems to last as long as root does.<br>Gedran<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
