	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi fellow DE Cleric,<br><br>Have you ever been told, that a cleric couldnt solo after lvl 20, well then, listen carefully to this.<br><br>When DryBones, Giant Skellies and Ghouls cons green to you, you have to move on to single pull NOT undead foes (except spectres). To be able to kill them, you need luck, mana, courage, and an item og great powers.<br><br>Have you ever tried to root a mob, nearly killed it, and then fled the battle, decause the mob broke out of the spell, tracked you down, and kept beating you for 50, 50, 50 ,50......... <br><br>Well, here is what to be done......<br><br>NOTE: For Dark Elven Clerics only.....<br><br>Do the regent of Innoruuk quest. Information is found at this very url.<br><br>Cast the Clinging darkness on the mob, fear the mob. Strike or Wrath the mob, beat the mob. If the spell wears off. Cast Holy might. Cast clinging darkness again, and repeat the circle again.<br><br>notice, that the Holy Might spell, will be in effect for a period of time, just long enough to cast another Clinging darkness spell.<br><br>I have killed druids, werebats, wererats, gnolls, vendors, centaurs and mammoths this way.<br><br>If the strategy looks alot like the necromancers favorite way of soloing, and yes, the principles are much alike.<br><br>Try it, give me comments, and feel free to email me with questions and comments if you like<br><br>Dark greetings<br><br>Sangreal Soulburner<br>CT<br>Sangreal@mail.dk<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
