	   <tr><td colspan=2>Thanks for the comment,<br><br>A few clarifications are probably needed. <br><br>I have spent a large amount of time in Unrest soloing and part of the time working in groups. Most of this was geared towards someone who can't find a group and still wants to do something. It is not easy, and is a long road.<br><br>At 13 Furor works well against death beetles, the problem is that casting it does a max of 19 damage, and it will take close to a full bar of mana to finish it off. <br><br>Spook the dead can be a life saver if you have multiple undead and you need to run to the zone. I have used spook the dead to scare off the undead on me, and cast divine aura to make the run. Just be sure to yell train to zone because this will create some pretty nice yard trash trains.<br><br>Other than that, Thanks Gedran, good info. :-)<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Lenda Helpinghand<br>Blood Inferno<br>Brell Serellis</td></tr>
