<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9674419571816></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9674419571816><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=9674419571816>Blunt Force: Clerical Weapontry</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=607><span id=Sage>Gedran</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>97 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 28th 1:52 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Every class on Everquest has acess to the use of, and advancement in, blunt weapons.  Clerics however, are the only class that must stick only to those weapons.<br>Clerical weapons break down into two obvious classes.  1 handed blunt, and 2 handed blunt.  Which you decide to use later on is up to you.<br><br>1 handed blunt has the advantage of usually being faster than most 2 handed weapons.  It is also your starting weapon, and probably the one you will use most frequently at lower levels.  Most of the 2 handed blunt weapons at newbie range are so pitiful, that it is almost a must to use a 1hb until you can reach a decent 2 handed weapon.  Also, because of there lower delay, these weapons are good for fighting caster Mobs and Players do to their low delay.  Later on, some of the 1hb's get a magical striking addition, Examples of these include, Hammer of wrath, Screaming mace, Cold Iron Morningstar, Enameled Black Mace.  And later stat increases, such as from the Wraith Bone Hammer, and Sharkbone warhammer.  The downfall to the 1handed is that they don't gain quite as many stats, procs, or effects as do the 2 handed, nor do they have the same damage as most 2 handeds do.<br><br>2 handed blunt weapons, while they are pitiful at the start, with the rusty 2 handed hammer, and worn great staff, not only having terrible delay, but also non spectacular damage, are much better later in the game.  2 handeds like the Staff of the Observers and the Runed Totem Staff, have good effects and procs, that can be afford at some times by lower teens players.  The damage on the later weapons, and even on the FS greatstaff, are impressive, FS alone dishing out 19 damage.  But while some 2 handers have average delay, most are much, much slower than their 1 handed counterparts.  Also, these staffs are much harder to get than the 1 handers, there are less of them about, and the quests involving obtaining one are also more difficult to complete.<br>Myself, I have stayed close to 1 handed blunt as a High Elf cleric the entire time.  I have found the delay to be invaluable and weapons that sometimes even rival the bonuses of a 2 handed blunt weapon.<br>I'm sure others have many more reasons for both 1 and 2 handers, so I will be happy to update this post from replies.<br>Gedran<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
